<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Iran (
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola, J" journalOrPublisher="Stuttgarter Beitraege zur Naturkunde aus dem Staatlichen Museum fuer Naturkunde in Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 24" refId="B6" refString="Dlabola, J, 1960b. Iranische Zikaden (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha): Ergebnisse der entomologischen Reisen Willi Richter, Stuttgart, im Iran 1954 und 1956-Nr. 31. Stuttgarter Beitraege zur Naturkunde aus dem Staatlichen Museum fuer Naturkunde in Stuttgart 41: 1 - 24" title="Iranische Zikaden (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha): Ergebnisse der entomologischen Reisen Willi Richter, Stuttgart, im Iran 1954 und 1956 - Nr. 31." volume="41" year="1960 b">Dlabola 1960b</bibRefCitation>
); Oman, Saudi Arabia (present study) (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 75–79" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 75 - 79. 75, 76. Distribution of Opsius spp. 75. World distribution (point indicates presence in the country). 76. Local distribution; 77 - 79. Habitats of Opsius spp. 77. Locality: Muzahimiyah, Al Khararah: 24 ° 24.35 ' N, 46 ° 14.67 ' E; 78. Locality: Abha, Sad Abha: 18 ° 19.32 ' N, 42 ° 31.00 ' E; 79. Type locality: Jazan, Wadi Jazan: 17 ° 01.275 ' N, 42 ° 59.187 ' E." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.67.46662.figures75-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371710" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">75</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 75–79" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 75 - 79. 75, 76. Distribution of Opsius spp. 75. World distribution (point indicates presence in the country). 76. Local distribution; 77 - 79. Habitats of Opsius spp. 77. Locality: Muzahimiyah, Al Khararah: 24 ° 24.35 ' N, 46 ° 14.67 ' E; 78. Locality: Abha, Sad Abha: 18 ° 19.32 ' N, 42 ° 31.00 ' E; 79. Type locality: Jazan, Wadi Jazan: 17 ° 01.275 ' N, 42 ° 59.187 ' E." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.67.46662.figures75-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371710" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">76</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and biology.</emphasis>
The abundance of this species varied phenologically between areas of the southwestern region of KSA. Peak abundance in Asir Province occurred in March, whereas in Jazan Province, the peak abundance occurred in January. Most specimens were collected by using light traps, but numerous specimens were also collected in Jazan Province from 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tamarix" order="Violales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Tamarix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. with a sweep net and by a portable vacuuming device. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dlabola" authorityYear="1960" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Opsius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opsius richteri" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="richteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Opsius richteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprised approximately 36% of the total number of specimens of this genus examined from KSA. This species was especially abundant at Wadi Qounonah, Asir Province, KSA (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 75–79" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 75 - 79. 75, 76. Distribution of Opsius spp. 75. World distribution (point indicates presence in the country). 76. Local distribution; 77 - 79. Habitats of Opsius spp. 77. Locality: Muzahimiyah, Al Khararah: 24 ° 24.35 ' N, 46 ° 14.67 ' E; 78. Locality: Abha, Sad Abha: 18 ° 19.32 ' N, 42 ° 31.00 ' E; 79. Type locality: Jazan, Wadi Jazan: 17 ° 01.275 ' N, 42 ° 59.187 ' E." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.67.46662.figures75-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371710" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">77-79</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. richteri" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="richteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">O. richteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. scutellaris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">O. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the aedeagal shaft branches diverging but can be distinguished by produced crown, aedeagal shafts and dorsal process distinctively curved or bent inward at base, and shaft branches two times as wide as basal process.
</paragraph>
